# ESLint Config Rules

- Never introduce circular imports between config entrypoints.
- Keep framework layering explicit: `common -> react -> next`, `common -> svelte`.
- Use safe fallbacks for environment-dependent logic (for example missing `.gitignore`).
- Add framework-specific rules in framework files, not in `common`.
- Keep plugin imports minimal; do not import duplicate stylistic presets across layers.

## Export Conventions

- Provide dedicated subpath configs (`/eslint-common`, `/eslint-react`, `/eslint-next`, `/eslint-svelte`).
- Keep root index exports stable and typed.
- When changing rule severity defaults, document the reason in PR/commit.

